[{"id":"VR625278","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are shown. In Figure 1, a small circle representing a satellite of mass lowercase m is at a distance of D from the center of a large circle representing an asteroid of mass uppercase M. In Figure 2, a small circle that represents the satellite of mass one half lowercase m is at a distance of 2 D from the center of the large circle that represents the asteroid of mass uppercase M.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR625278.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">In Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, a satellite of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"lowercase m\"><math alttext=\"lowercase m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span> is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D\"><math alttext=\"D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>D</mi></math></span></span> from the center of an asteroid of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase M\"><math alttext=\"uppercase M\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>M</mi></math></span></span>. The satellite then fires its thrusters to move away from the asteroid and when it reaches a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2 D\"><math alttext=\"2 D\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mi>D</mi></math></span></span> from the center of the asteroid, its mass is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction lowercase m over 2\"><math alttext=\"the fraction lowercase m over 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></span></span>, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. What is the change in the gravitational potential energy of the asteroid-satellite system between Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR625278_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator G lowercase m, uppercase M, and denominator 4 D, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator G lowercase m, uppercase M, and denominator 4 D, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator G lowercase m, uppercase M, and denominator 2 D, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator G lowercase m, uppercase M, and denominator 2 D, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator 3 G lowercase m, uppercase M, and denominator 4 D, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator 3 G lowercase m, uppercase M, and denominator 4 D, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction with numerator 5 G lowercase m, uppercase M, and denominator 4 D, end fraction\"><math alttext=\"the fraction with numerator 5 G lowercase m, uppercase M, and denominator 4 D, end fraction\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>G</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>D</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]